# Civil Takeoff Flow — 3-Pass Architecture

## Why Civil Plans Are Different

Civil plan sets (grading, utilities, roadway, drainage) have a drafting convention that breaks standard chunking:

- **Keynote numbers reset per sheet** — keynote "3" on sheet C-101 is a different material than keynote "3" on sheet C-102
- **Cross-sheet context is required** — a pipe run started on C-101 may continue on C-102
- **Scales vary per sheet** — a single PDF may have 1"=20' on one sheet and 1"=40' on another
- **Multi-sheet aggregation must be by material category**, never by keynote number

Chunking civil plans the same way as residential (5 pages per API call) produces wildly incorrect quantities. The 3-pass flow solves this.

---

## 3-Pass Flow — Implementation

### Entry Point

```javascript
export async function runTakeoff(fileBuffer, mimeType, options = {}) {
  const { useCustomProject = false, planType = 'auto' } = options;

  // Branch to civil flow only when explicitly civil AND it's a PDF
  if (planType === 'civil' && mimeType === 'application/pdf') {
    return await runTakeoffCivil(fileBuffer, options);
  }

  return await runTakeoffDefault(fileBuffer, mimeType, options);
}
```

### Pass 1 — Keynote Register Extraction

```javascript
async function runTakeoffCivil(fileBuffer, options) {
  const { useCustomProject = false } = options;

  // Extract only page 1 for the register
  const page1Buffer = await extractPdfPage(fileBuffer, 1); // uses pdf-lib

  const registerResponse = await anthropic.messages.create({
    model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6',
    max_tokens: 2000,
    messages: [{
      role: 'user',
      content: [
        { type: 'document', source: { type: 'base64', media_type: 'application/pdf', data: page1Buffer.toString('base64') } },
        { type: 'text', text: buildKeynoteRegisterPrompt() }
      ]
    }]
  });

  const keynoteRegister = parseJsonResponse(registerResponse);
  const totalPages = await getPdfPageCount(fileBuffer); // uses pdf-lib

  // Pass 2 — per-sheet takeoffs
  return await runCivilSheetPass(fileBuffer, keynoteRegister, totalPages, useCustomProject);
}
```

### Pass 2 — Per-Sheet Takeoffs

```javascript
async function runCivilSheetPass(fileBuffer, keynoteRegister, totalPages, useCustomProject) {
  const sheetResults = [];

  for (let pageNum = 1; pageNum <= totalPages; pageNum++) {
    const pageBuffer = await extractPdfPage(fileBuffer, pageNum);
    const prompt = buildSheetTakeoffPrompt(keynoteRegister, pageNum, totalPages, useCustomProject);

    const response = await anthropic.messages.create({
      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6',
      max_tokens: 4000,
      messages: [{
        role: 'user',
        content: [
          { type: 'document', source: { type: 'base64', media_type: 'application/pdf', data: pageBuffer.toString('base64') } },
          { type: 'text', text: prompt }
        ]
      }]
    });

    const sheetData = parseJsonResponse(response);
    sheetData._sourceSheet = `Page ${pageNum}`;
    sheetResults.push(sheetData);
  }

  // Pass 3 — aggregate
  return aggregateCivilSheets(sheetResults);
}
```

### Pass 3 — Aggregation

```javascript
function aggregateCivilSheets(sheetResults) {
  const itemMap = {};

  for (const sheet of sheetResults) {
    for (const category of (sheet.material_takeoff ?? [])) {
      for (const item of (category.items ?? [sheet.material_takeoff].flat())) {
        // ✅ CORRECT: key by category + description
        const key = `${item.category}||${item.description}`.toLowerCase().trim();

        // ❌ NEVER key by keynote number — keynotes reset per sheet
        // const key = item.keynote_number  // WRONG — DO NOT DO THIS

        if (itemMap[key]) {
          itemMap[key].quantity += (item.quantity ?? 0);
          itemMap[key].drawing_refs = [...new Set([
            ...(itemMap[key].drawing_refs ?? []),
            ...(item.drawing_refs ?? [sheet._sourceSheet])
          ])];
          // Merge assumptions, deduplicate
          itemMap[key].assumptions = [...new Set([
            ...(itemMap[key].assumptions ?? []),
            ...(item.assumptions ?? [])
          ])];
          // Downgrade confidence if any sheet had lower confidence
          if (item.confidence === 'low') itemMap[key].confidence = 'low';
          else if (item.confidence === 'medium' && itemMap[key].confidence !== 'low') {
            itemMap[key].confidence = 'medium';
          }
        } else {
          itemMap[key] = {
            ...item,
            drawing_refs: item.drawing_refs ?? [sheet._sourceSheet],
            sourceSheets: [sheet._sourceSheet]
          };
        }
      }
    }
  }

  return {
    project_summary: sheetResults[0]?.project_summary ?? {},
    material_takeoff: Object.values(itemMap),
    total_categories: new Set(Object.values(itemMap).map(i => i.category)).size,
    missing_information: sheetResults.flatMap(s => s.missing_information ?? []),
    confidence_score: deriveOverallConfidence(Object.values(itemMap))
  };
}
```

